definition.value: A sample introduction medium designates the material type that is used as medium (role) in a sample introduction process in a measurement. [Allotrope]
A measurement mode setting is a control setting that specifies the measurement mode of some measurement process. [Allotrope]
A detector relative offset setting is a detector setting that specifies the offset of the signals of two detectors to align them along the x-axis. [Allotrope]
A m/z minimum setting is a m/z setting that specifies the minimum mass per charge ratio of a scan. [Allotrope]
A m/z maximum setting is a m/z setting that specifies the maximum mass per charge ratio of a scan. [Allotrope]
A data processing aggregate document is a document that aggregates data processing documents. [Allotrope]
A data processing document is a document that encompasses the metadata associated with a data processing operation. [Allotrope]
A data processing type is a classification datum that classifies the type of data processing performed. [Allotrope]
A data format specification type is a classification datum that classifies the data format used to store data. [Allotrope]
A processed data aggregate document is a document that aggregates processed data documents. [Allotrope]
A processed data document is a document that encompasses the output of some data processing operation. [Allotrope]
A data processing description is a description of some data processing operation. [Allotrope]
A maximum row setting is a control setting specifying a maximum row of pixels in a raster image. [Allotrope]
A foam detection sensitivity setting is a control setting that specifies the sensitivity for detection of foam. [Allotrope]
A smoothing window setting is a control setting that specifies the smoothing window for foam detection. [Allotrope]
A pixel density is a figure facet that quantifies the number of pixels per unit size of some image. [Allotrope]
A liquid start row is the minimum row of pixels in a raster image where a liquid is detected. [Allotrope]
A liquid end row is the maximum row of pixels in a raster image where a liquid is detected. [Allotrope]
A foam detection result is an assay result that specifies whether foam was detected. [Allotrope]
A foam start row is the minimum row of pixels in a raster image where a foam is detected. [Allotrope]
A foam end row is the maximum row of pixels in a raster image where a foam is detected. [Allotrope]
A liquid row count is a count of the number of rows of pixels in a raster image where liquid is detected. [Allotrope]
A foam row count is a count of the number of rows of pixels in a raster image where foam is detected, including any air gap if present. [Allotrope]
A total row count is a count of the number of rows of pixels in a raster image where any liquid or foam is detected. [Allotrope]
A liquid height is a height of some liquid. [Allotrope]
A total foam height is a height of some foam, including any air gap if present. [Allotrope]
A total material height is the summation of heights of some collection of materials. [Allotrope]
An air gap detection result is an assay result that specifies whether an air gap was detected. [Allotrope]
A normalized foam row count is a count of the number of rows of pixels in a raster image where foam is detected, excluding any air gap if present. [Allotrope]
A normalized foam height is a height of some foam, excluding any air gap if present. [Allotrope]
An above gap foam row count is a count of the number of rows of pixels in a raster image where foam is detected above an air gap. [Allotrope]
A below gap foam row count is a count of the number of rows of pixels in a raster image where foam is detected below an air gap. [Allotrope]
A liquid homogeneity gradient is a description describing the magnitude of the difference between the foam and liquid sides of an extrapolated boundary in a sample. [Allotrope]
An exception description is a description of some unexpected, unusual or unintended situation. [Allotrope]
A bubble aggregate document is a document that aggregates bubble documents. [Allotrope]
A bubble document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a bubble. [Allotrope]
A pixel count is a count of the number of pixels in some raster image. [Allotrope]
An eccentricity is a quality quantification facet that quantifies some eccentricity. [Allotrope]
A relative location is a location facet that denotes a location of an entity relative to some other entity. [Allotrope]
A centroid y-coordinate is a y-coordinate for the center point of some entity. [Allotrope]
A centroid x-coordinate is a x-coordinate for the center point of some entity. [Allotrope]
A barcode is a method of representing data in a visual, machine-readable form. [Wikipedia]
A linear velocity datum is a quality quantification facet that quantifies how fast an object is traveling in a straight line, meaning its direction is not changing. [Allotrope]
Height is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the bearer's vertical dimension of extension. [Allotrope]
A pixel is a figure facet that is the smallest addressable element in a raster image. [Wikipedia]
A raster image is an image represented as a rectangular matrix or grid of square pixels, viewable via a computer display, paper, or other display medium. [Wikipedia]
A foam height is a height of some foam. [Allotrope]
A statistics aggregate document is a document that aggregates statistics documents. [Allotrope]
A statistics document is a document that encapsulates the statistical information associated with some population. [Allotrope]

A statistical feature is a statistical facet that defines the feature with the role of a description or classification of a property, characteristic or facet of the members of the aggregate that is common to each member and is used to make aggregated data about the aggregate. [Allotrope]
